<FeaturePage
  title="Automatic Backups"
  description="Continuous point-in-time snapshots. Roll back to any moment with a single click."
  badge="Cloud · Managed"
  activePath="/cloud"
>
  <p>
    sp00ky Cloud runs continuous snapshots of every workspace in the background. Snapshots are
    incremental, encrypted, and indexed by time — so rolling back to yesterday at 14:32 is the
    same effort as rolling back to five minutes ago.
  </p>
  <p>
    No pipelines, no cron jobs, no support tickets. Open the dashboard, pick a point in time,
    click restore. Optional scheduled exports push snapshots to your own object storage.
  </p>
  <h2>What’s covered</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Continuous incremental snapshots — seconds-level granularity.</li>
    <li>One-click restore to any point in time.</li>
    <li>Encrypted at rest; opaque to the storage layer.</li>
    <li>Optional export to S3, GCS, or R2.</li>
  </ul>
</FeaturePage>
